    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "_I answered by email but also answering here for visibility._\r\n​\r\n​Mocking the request when there is no query should work.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst algoliaClient = algoliasearch(\r\n  \"latency\",\r\n  \"6be0576ff61c053d5f9a3225e2a90f76\"\r\n);\r\n\r\nconst searchClient = {\r\n  search(requests) {\r\n    if (requests.every(({ params }) => !params.query)) {\r\n      return Promise.resolve({\r\n        results: requests.map(() => ({\r\n          hits: [],\r\n          nbHits: 0,\r\n          processingTimeMS: 0,\r\n        })),\r\n      });\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return algoliaClient.search(requests);\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you only want the very first empty query to be skipped, you can add a boolean flag to ignore the check for the next searches.​",
